Well there are dozen solutions at least, some were already suggested (by Rhombus for example).<br>
Read the whole thread.<br>
<br>
Some fast adjustements to the pet:<br>
Get rid of all Wiz spells on it (keep the snare i care a fuck about snare and i think Mages overestimate snare and root anyway grossly).<br>
Make it a level 44-49 Magician, you have great spells at that level - that great that VI had to give us delayed the rent spell to be remotly competitve to your spells in that level range.<br>
<br>
If you want to have it cast Wiz spells, limit it to level 44 max wiz spells. We have great spells at that level too, Conflag etc, Force Strike, Lightning Shock, Ice Shock, etc.<br>
<br>
Who said that 90 DPS is appropriate for a Pet? I don't think it is appropriate, don't forget you will nuke, too, and you are already a DPS hoag.<br>
<br>
Instead make the pet maybe immune to AE spells, so it is an asset to the usual raid force.<br>
<br>
You want a reason why to summon that pet? Give it something unique, but without stepping on other classes' toes.<br>
Give it (Wiz) spells up to level 44 MAX, and make it immune to AEs, make it cast most of the time, so it becomes an additional and reasonable force in raids.<br>
<br>
You have to keep in mind that all that kind of stuff has to stay balanced.<br>
If you want to have it a player summoned fire pet cast Ice Comet, give Wizards a 2.5K Ice based nuke at level 62.<br>
<br>
And Froz, i really don't care about casting efficiency nad spell casting times on our other ice based spells. I know those data AS well as you do know it. But you miss completly my point.  IoS and ADoI are designed after the IC modell, that's a fact and i don't think it is appropriate to have a high level research spell (<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>that is till level 60 the highest avaiable Ice nuke for our class</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->) on a Pet. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=natanmagus>Natan Magus</A> at: 5/19/03 10:28:16 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gebbly>Gebbly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 272<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/03 10:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> debate is good</span><hr size=1> HataTheMage, admittedly there are certain people here who are just upset at some of the possibilities but there are also some here who are trying to make constructive criticism.<br>
